body:
Implements the dynamic part of https://github.com/PrismarineJS/node-minecraft-protocol/issues/234 Cross version support

Ported from https://github.com/deathcap/node-minecraft-protocol-auto (which I can deprecate if this is merged)

To do:

* [x] Enhance createClient() to allow waiting/pausing so it can be reconfigured before connect -- src/client/setProtocol.js? (installs client.on('connect') listener)
* [x] Change the protocol negotiation to be supported with a createClient()-compatible API (vs createClientAsync)
* [x] Update to use minecraft-data protocolVersions
* [x] Move into src/client/ to act as plugin/middleware

comment_data.body: Why client.options ? The `client, options` pattern is consistent with what mineflayer is doing, and it seems to makes sense. (It also allows destructuring : for example https://github.com/PrismarineJS/flying-squid/blob/master/src/lib/plugins/world.js#L10 )

Ah I saw your commit message "This allows client plugins to change the options on the client object,
and have it reflected in other plugins. Previously, had to rely on the
options being the same object, and hold a reference to it. Now it is
always accessible as `client.options`."

It sounds like it assume some order of execution between plugins. Which plugins is accessing the modified property ?
this can be removed now (with minecraft-data 0.19.1)

commit.message: Add dynamic cross-protocol support

Add wait_connect option, to require 'connect_allowed' event before src/client/setProtocol proceeds

Intended to allow clients to configure the client object before any data
is sent, specifically, before src/client/setProtocol sends the
set_protocol packet.
Fix unintentional var client declaration
Update to use compatible sync API (createClient)
Use minecraft-data for protocol version -> minecraft version

Move options to client object

This allows client plugins to change the options on the client object,
and have it reflected in other plugins. Previously, had to rely on the
options being the same object, and hold a reference to it. Now it is
always accessible as `client.options`.
Rename src/createClientAuto.js -> src/client/autoVersion.js
Remove useless statement
Support options.version==false in createClient() to auto-detect version
Set state property instead of setSerializer() to ensure serializers are properly piped
Use new object for ping() to avoid potential cross-contamination
Update client connect() for options move compatibility
Update documentation for version:false option
Pre-Netty protocol versions are not supported yet
Update to minecraft-data ^0.19.0
Update minecraft-data to use GitHub dependency on PrismarineJS/node-minecraft-data
Try using git commit hash to node-minecraft-data
Try to clone minecraft-data to workaround https://github.com/PrismarineJS/node-minecraft-data/issues/16
Update to minecraft-data ^0.19.1
Lookup version using minecraft-data postNettyVersionsByProtocolVersion
Move options back to client parameters
Move wait_connect to client object
